text: hi everyone today I'm making baked it
cassava cake it's a very popular Asian
dessert it is super easy to make but the
final product will make you happy
you will need frozen credit cassava
coconut milk sugar shredded coconut some
vegetable oil salt and vanilla the first
thing you want to do is to preheat the
oven 280 degrees Celsius then bring out
the excess water from the grated frozen
cassava with a strainer or a cloth then
mix all ingredients together this is a
small can of coconut milk hundred
sixty-five ml for sugar you can use
either brown sugar or a granulated sugar
I use 1/3 cup but of course you can
adjust your taste and then 3/4 cup
shredded coconut I also bought frozen 1
tbsp vegetable or a and 1/4 TSP of salt
and then 1 pack of vanilla sugar or you
can also use a vanilla extract mix
everything with the grated cassava until
everything else combined
you
increase your baking pan with some
vegetable oil or cooking spray and using
a silicone baking pan so actually I
don't need to do that and pouring your
mixture and then flatten the surface
with a spool this pan has 20 centimeter
diameter so the cake cannot be 1 inch
thick bake for about 50 to 60 minutes
until it is gone when you insert a
toothpick in the center of the cake and
it's come out clean is done you have to
let it cool completely before cutting
when the KE cone and set you remove it
from the baking pan and then cut into a
pie site pieces I use brown sugar so
it's a little darker in color I think
for a nice presentation normally people
cut it in diamond shape and arrange in a
way that is look like a flower but of
course you don't have to do that the
cake is rather a flexible and a
glutinous it has a great flavor of
coconut and cassava I didn't add any add
among things because I just love the
pure flavor of cassava I hope you will
turn out this recipe and let me know
